            <pb/>
            <hi rend="smallcaps">Curious Advertisement </hi>
            <lb/>From the<hi rend="smallcaps">Pittsburgh Gazette</hi> 
         </p>
         <p>
            <hi rend="italic">Pittsburgh, Dec.</hi>  23, 1789.</p>
         <p> JULY the twenty-seventh day <lb/>My wife Betsey ran away <lb/>From bed and board,â€“and this did say, <lb/>"She would no longer with me stay." <lb/>Since she has left me without cause <lb/>I'll give her time enough to pause. <lb/>That she may see her grievous error, <lb/>When I live happy with a fairer. <lb/>So I forewarn both great and small <lb/>To trust her any thing at all, <lb/>For of her contracts from this day <lb/>One farthing's worth I will not pay. <lb/>
            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dennis O'Bryan</hi> 
         </p>
